title.narrative: Laguna de Bay Institutional Strengthening and Community Participation/LISCOP

description.narrative: The overarching objective of the proposed project is to assist the Laguna Lake Development Authority (LLDA), Local Government Units(LGUs) and other stakeholders to improve the environmental quality of the Laguna De Bay watershed.This will be achieved through: (i) behavioral changes and activities undertaken by watershed users to improve the environmental quality o f the lake and its watershed; and, (ii) improved planning, regulatory instruments and incentives, and participation in the environmental management o f the Laguna de Bay watershed.

condition.narrative: Commitment of LLDA, the DENR and the Department of Finance set forth in the Institutional Memorandum of Agreement to implement theproject
LLDA to submit its re-rengineered structure based in the LIDO to the Department of Budget and Management for approval
The Department of Environment and Natural Resources to provide the annual budget cover to implement subprojects under Component 1
The project to follow the agreed environmental and social safeguards framework during implementation
The project to follow the agreed financial management arrangements and maintain a financial management system, including recordsand accounts and financial statements acceptable to the Bank
The project to follow the agreed procurement guidelines during implementation
